Rating: 3
To Sandro from Bidart... I am French. This recipe is good & easy. You do NOT have to marinate a Boeuf Bourguignon in wine for a day (or for any time at all). A full-bodied red wine is generally added after you saute the beef & vegetables in hot oil & bacon fat. Obviously there are variations on the basic recipe but marinating is not required. Refer to 'Mastering the Art of French Cooking' by Simone Beck, L. Bertholle & Julia Child for a really classic Boeuf Bourguignon.

